OL,3,CMan admits killing wife after police
OL,4,Cdiscover body on welfare call
OL,6,FA man has admitted killing his wife
OL,7,Fafter her body was discovered in a
OL,8,Fhouse by police who had been called
OL,9,Fout due to concerns for their welfare.
OL,11,FThe husband has entered a guilty plea
OL,12,Fto a count of manslaughter but
OL,13,Fcontinues to deny murder.
OL,15,FMichael Davies, 57, killed his wife
OL,16,FTracey Davies, 48, who was found dead
OL,17,Fat a property in Cefn Cribwr, near
OL,18,FBridgend on April 18. The defendant
OL,19,Fwas arrested at the scene and later
OL,20,Fcharged with her murder.
